4.12	Ikue_Asazaki	Ikue Asazaki	Ikue Asazaki Asazaki Ikue) (born 11 November 1935) is a Japanese folk singer from Kagoshima. She was born in Kedomi, Amami Islands. She grew up on the Amami Islands (in Setouchi, Kagoshima) which are famous for spawning popular singers of traditional Ryukyuan Music. Her father influenced her early music strongly during her upbringing. Her musical style sometimes is resembling the style of New Age. One of her most famous albums is "Utabautayun" with traditional Ryukyuan songs and lyrics. And "Minya", with Akira Takahashi accompanying her on the piano.	
